{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848909515,"sessionID":"ses_287298a3dffeEHmZ2pDXms5xG9","part":{"id":"prt_d78d7ea760014fo6z82tu2J96b","messageID":"msg_d78d6da6d001IX7lHbP77r4vjc","sessionID":"ses_287298a3dffeEHmZ2pDXms5xG9","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_tool-f763037740d94e7b8c74bcdcc98bc4dd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","newString":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/router`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create package directory structure and documentation\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router` package directory\n- [ ] Create `doc.go` with package documentation\n- [ ] Create `README.md` with package overview\n- [ ] Add Go module imports for dependencies\n  - [ ] `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`\n  - [ ] `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n  - [ ] `golang.org/x/net/http2`\n  - [ ] `k8s.io/client-go`\n  - [ ] `k8s.io/klog/v2`\n  - [ ] Internal dependencies (`pkg/store`, `pkg/common/types`, `pkg/api`)\n- [ ] Verify package structure compiles\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/router` to ensure package structure is valid\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Implement configuration structure\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/config.go`\n- [ ] Define `Config` struct with fields:\n  - [ ] `Port string` - Server port (default: \"8080\")\n  - [ ] `Debug bool` - Debug mode flag\n  - [ ] `EnableTLS bool` - TLS enablement flag\n  - [ ] `TLSCert string` - TLS certificate path\n  - [ ] `TLSKey string` - TLS key path\n  - [ ] `MaxConcurrentRequests int` - Concurrency limit (default: 1000)\n  - [ ] `WorkloadManagerURL string` - Workload manager endpoint\n  - [ ] `AgentcubeNamespace string` - Router namespace (default: \"default\")\n- [ ] Implement `DefaultConfig()` function returning default configuration\n- [ ] Implement `LoadConfig() error` function to load from environment variables\n- [ ] Add validation logic for required configuration fields\n- [ ] Create `config_test.go` with unit tests for configuration loading\n  - [ ] `TestDefaultConfig`\n  - [ ] `TestLoadConfigFromEnv`\n  - [ ] `TestConfigValidation`\n  - [ ] `TestMissingRequiredConfig`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig` to ensure configuration handling works correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Implement common types and data structures\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/types.go`\n- [ ] Define `SandboxInfo` struct with all required fields\n  - [ ] `Kind string` - \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n  - [ ] `SandboxID string` - Unique identifier\n  - [ ] `SandboxName string` - Pod name\n  - [ ] `SandboxNamespace string` - Pod namespace\n  - [ ] `Name string` - Resource name\n  - [ ] `EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint` - Service endpoints\n  - [ ] `SessionID string` - Session identifier\n  - [ ] `CreatedAt time.Time` - Creation timestamp\n  - [ ] `ExpiresAt time.Time` - Expiration timestamp\n  - [ ] `Status string` - Sandbox status\n  - [ ] `PodIP string` - Pod IP address\n  - [ ] `WorkloadName string` - Workload name\n  - [ ] `Namespace string` - Resource namespace\n  - [ ] `LastActivityAt time.Time` - Last activity timestamp\n- [ ] Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct\n  - [ ] `Path string` - URL path prefix\n  - [ ] `Protocol string` - \"http\" or \"https\"\n  - [ ] `Endpoint string` - Target URL endpoint\n- [ ] Define `ErrorResponse` struct\n  - [ ] `Error string` - Error message\n  - [ ] `Code string` - Error code (optional)\n- [ ] Define `JWTClaims` struct\n  - [ ] `SessionID string`\n  - [ ] `jwt.RegisteredClaims`\n- [ ] Add JSON tags for all struct fields\n- [ ] Create `types_test.go` with struct validation tests\n  - [ ] `TestSandboxInfoJSONSerialization`\n  - [ ] `TestErrorResponseJSONSerialization`\n  - [ ] `TestSandboxEntryPointValidation`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestTypes` and verify JSON serialization works correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Implement JWT manager for authentication\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- [ ] Define `JWTManager` struct\n  - [ ] `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n  - [ ] `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n  - [ ] `clientset kubernetes.Interface`\n  - [ ] `namespace string`\n- [ ] Implement `NewJWTManager()` constructor function\n- [ ] Implement `GenerateToken()` method\n  - [ ] Create JWT claims with session ID\n  - [ ] Set token expiration (5 minutes)\n  - [ ] Sign token with RSA private key\n  - [ ] Return signed token string\n- [ ] Implement `ValidateToken()` method\n  - [ ] Parse and verify token signature\n  - [ ] Extract session ID from claims\n  - [ ] Validate token expiration\n  - [ ] Return session ID or error\n- [ ] Implement `generateRSAKeyPair()` private method\n  - [ ] Generate 2048-bit RSA key pair\n  - [ ] Return private and public keys\n- [ ] Implement `storeOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` method\n  - [ ] Check for existing Kubernetes secret\n  - [ ] Load keys from secret if exists\n  - [ ] Generate and store new keys if not exists\n- [ ] Implement `storeJWTKeySecret()` private method\n  - [ ] Create/update Kubernetes secret\n  - [ ] Store RSA keys as base64-encoded values\n- [ ] Create `jwt_test.go` with comprehensive tests\n  - [ ] `TestGenerateToken`\n  - [ ] `TestValidateToken`\n  - [ ] `TestTokenExpiration`\n  - [ ] `TestInvalidTokenSignature`\n  - [ ] `TestExpiredToken`\n  - [ ] `TestGenerateRSAKeyPair`\n  - [ ] `TestStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` (mock Kubernetes client)\n  - [ ] `TestKeyRotation`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWT` to verify JWT operations work correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Implement session manager for sandbox lookup\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- [ ] Define `SessionManager` interface\n  - [ ] `GetSandboxBySession()` method signature\n- [ ] Define `manager` struct implementing SessionManager\n  - [ ] `storeClient store.Store`\n  - [ ] `workloadMgrAddr string`\n  - [ ] `httpClient *http.Client`\n- [ ] Implement `NewSessionManager()` constructor function\n- [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySession()` method\n  - [ ] Generate cache key from session parameters\n  - [ ] Try to retrieve sandbox info from store cache\n  - [ ] On cache miss, call workload manager\n  - [ ] Store response in cache with TTL\n  - [ ] Return sandbox info\n- [ ] Implement `getSandboxFromWorkloadManager()` private method\n  - [ ] Build HTTP request to workload manager\n  - [ ] Handle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter kinds\n  - [ ] Parse response into SandboxInfo\n  - [ ] Handle HTTP errors\n- [ ] Implement `generateCacheKey()` helper method\n- [ ] Implement `storeInCache()` private method\n  - [ ] Serialize SandboxInfo to JSON\n  - [ ] Store with appropriate TTL\n  - [ ] Handle store errors gracefully\n- [ ] Create `session_manager_test.go` with tests\n  - [ ] `TestGetSandboxBySession_CacheHit`\n  - [ ] `TestGetSandboxBySession_CacheMiss`\n  - [ ] `TestGetSandboxFromWorkloadManager_AgentRuntime`\n  - [ ] `TestGetSandboxFromWorkloadManager_CodeInterpreter`\n  - [ ] `TestWorkloadManagerErrorHandling`\n  - [ ] `TestCacheTTLExpiration` (mock time)\n  - [ ] `TestGenerateCacheKey`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager` to verify session management works correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Implement HTTP reverse proxy\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/proxy.go`\n- [ ] Define `ReverseProxy` struct\n  - [ ] `httpTransport *http.Transport`\n  - [ ] `jwtManager *JWTManager`\n- [ ] Implement `NewReverseProxy()` constructor function\n- [ ] Implement `configureHTTPTransport()` private method\n  - [ ] Enable HTTP/2 support\n  - [ ] Configure connection pooling\n  - [ ] Set TLS configuration\n  - [ ] Configure timeout values\n- [ ] Implement `ProxyRequest()` method\n  - [ ] Generate JWT token for authentication\n  - [ ] Create HTTP request to sandbox endpoint\n  - [ ] Copy original request headers\n  - [ ] Add authentication headers\n  - [ ] Execute proxy request\n  - [ ] Copy response headers\n  - [ ] Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - [ ] Stream response to client\n- [ ] Implement `modifyRequestHeaders()` helper method\n  - [ ] Forward relevant original headers\n  - [ ] Add authentication header\n  - [ ] Remove hop-by-hop headers\n- [ ] Implement `modifyResponseHeaders()` helper method\n  - [ ] Copy response headers\n  - [ ] Add session ID header\n  - [ ] Remove hop-by-hop headers\n- [ ] Create `proxy_test.go` with tests\n  - [ ] `TestProxyRequest_Success`\n  - [ ] `TestProxyRequest_JWTGeneration`\n  - [ ] `TestProxyRequest_HeaderModification`\n  - [ ] `TestProxyRequest_ResponseStreaming`\n  - [ ] `TestProxyRequest_BackendError`\n  - [ ] `TestHTTPTransportConfiguration`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestProxy` to verify reverse proxy functionality\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Implement middleware components\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n- [ ] Implement `concurrencyLimitMiddleware()` function\n  - [ ] Use semaphore for concurrency control\n  - [ ] Acquire semaphore before processing\n  - [ ] Release semaphore after processing\n  - [ ] Return 429 if limit exceeded\n  - [ ] Add appropriate response headers\n- [ ] Implement `loggingMiddleware()` function\n  - [ ] Log request method and path\n  - [ ] Log request duration\n  - [ ] Log response status code\n  - [ ] Add request ID to logs\n- [ ] Implement `recoveryMiddleware()` function\n  - [ ] Recover from panics\n  - [ ] Log panic stack trace\n  - [ ] Return 500 error response\n- [ ] Implement `correlationIDMiddleware()` function\n  - [ ] Generate or extract correlation ID\n  - [ ] Add to request context\n  - [ ] Return in response headers\n- [ ] Create `middleware_test.go` with tests\n  - [ ] `TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_UnderLimit`\n  - [ ] `TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_ExceedsLimit`\n  - [ ] `TestLoggingMiddleware`\n  - [ ] `TestRecoveryMiddleware`\n  - [ ] `TestCorrelationIDMiddleware`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddleware` to verify middleware functionality\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Implement HTTP handlers\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n- [ ] Define handler structs with dependencies\n- [ ] Implement `handleHealthLive()` function\n  - [ ] Return `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n  - [ ] Set appropriate HTTP status (200)\n  - [ ] No authentication required\n- [ ] Implement `handleHealthReady()` function\n  - [ ] Check session manager availability\n  - [ ] Return `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` or error\n  - [ ] Include error details if not ready\n- [ ] Implement `handleAgentInvoke()` function\n  - [ ] Extract namespace and name from path\n  - [ ] Extract or generate session ID\n  - [ ] Get sandbox info from session manager\n  - [ ] Proxy request to sandbox\n  - [ ] Handle all error cases\n- [ ] Implement `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke()` function\n  - [ ] Same flow as AgentRuntime invoke\n  - [ ] Use CodeInterpreter kind\n- [ ] Implement `extractSessionID()` helper method\n  - [ ] Check `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - [ ] Generate new session ID if not present\n- [ ] Implement `generateSessionID()` helper method\n  - [ ] Use UUID for session ID\n- [ ] Create `handlers_test.go` with tests\n  - [ ] `TestHandleHealthLive`\n  - [ ] `TestHandleHealthReady`\n  - [ ] `TestHandleAgentInvoke_Success`\n  - [ ] `TestHandleAgentInvoke_ExistingSession`\n  - [ ] `TestHandleAgentInvoke_NewSession`\n  - [ ] `TestHandleAgentInvoke_SandboxNotFound`\n  - [ ] `TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke`\n  - [ ] `TestExtractSessionID`\n  - [ ] `TestGenerateSessionID`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandlers` to verify handler functionality\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Implement HTTP server\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/server.go`\n- [ ] Define `Server` struct\n  - [ ] `config *Config`\n  - [ ] `engine *gin.Engine`\n  - [ ] `httpServer *http.Server`\n  - [ ] `sessionManager SessionManager`\n  - [ ] `storeClient store.Store`\n  - [ ] `httpTransport *http.Transport`\n  - [ ] `jwtManager *JWTManager`\n- [ ] Imp